                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1298">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115R39/5</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                            <gloss type="to">Special Representative Rodgers</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-17T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>216. Department’s July 14, 5 p.m.<note n="20" xml:id="d1298fn20">
                        <ref target="frus1916#pg_783">For. Rel. 1916, p. 783</ref>.</note> Simpich
                    reports interviewing Governor who states Richardson Company’s property was
                    seized because owned by country’s enemies; but now that war is avoided he is
                    ordering administrator to relinquish possession property.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
